<lb/><p rend="no-indent" n="address2 liv_020090_0001"><space extent="1" unit="words"/><space extent="1" unit="chars"/><placeName>16, Devonshire Chambers
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Bishopsgate Street Without,</placeName>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><placeName><settlement><seg rend="large">L</seg>ondon</settlement>, <hi rend="small">E.C.</hi></placeName> <date when="1882-04-24"><seg rend="italic" n="date liv_020090_0001">April 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi></seg> 18<seg rend="italic" n="date liv_020090_0001">82</seg></date></p>

<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><persName>Mrs. E. P. Nichols,</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>Dear Friend,</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="0" unit="chars"/>I have taken
<lb/>the liberty of dropping you a line
<lb/>to ask you if you will grant me one
<lb/>more favor and that is the sum of
<lb/>&#xa3;3. and if ever I apply to you
<lb/>again for assistance I trust you
<lb/>will not answer my application.
<lb/>I should have gone to <country>America</country>
<lb/>before this but my brother wrote
<lb/>me telling me it was advisable
<lb/>for me to stay here awhile yet

	<pb facs="liv_020090_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>on &#8448;. of some circumstances over
<lb/>which I had no control.
<lb/>I trust his letter to you was
<lb/>satisfactory.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent">Hoping your health remains good
<lb/>&amp; to hear from you soon, also
<lb/>craving your forgiveness for
<lb/>annoying you so much.</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/>I am,</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="3" unit="words"/><space extent="3" unit="chars"/>Yr. obt. servant,</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><persName>W.I. Craft.</persName></p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><seg rend="sub"><seg rend="large"><seg rend="sub">P.</seg><seg rend="small">S.</seg></seg></seg>
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>I purpose leaving <settlement>London</settlement> in the summer or Autumn
<lb/>for good.</p>
